Ina M. DIXON, Appellant, v. Adolphus O. EGGLETON, Appellee. No. 9967. United States Court of Appeals District of Columbia Circuit. Submitted May 10, 1949. Decided May 31, 1949. Mr. James Theodore Wright, Washington, D. C., submitted on brief for appellant. Mr. Lewis E. Barnes, Washington, D. C, submitted on brief for appellee.

Before CLARK, WILBUR K. MILLER and PRETTYMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

We find no substantial error in the record. The judgment of the District Court is- therefore affirmed.

Affirmed.
